RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 1 1 1/16M All Weather Track CR: 71. Maiden Claiming Purse 13500. FOR MAIDENS, FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Weight, 123 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LOOKOUT POINT rated off of the decent early pace, saved ground to the far turn, rallied four wide into the stretch run, dodged AFRICAN PRINCE when that one swerved in mid-stretch, closed fast inside of the furlong marker, came within aim in deep stretch and caught TIGER'S ARROW in the final strides to prevail. TIGER'S ARROW prominent into the first turn, attended to the decent fractions through the backstretch run, pressured then overtook RANCHO RED nearing the top of the lane, drew to a clear lead in mid-stretch, remained clear to the sixteenth-marker, was caught by the winner in the final strides and held safely for second. SHANAGOLDEN bobbled at the start, took back off of the loose leaders through the backstretch run, roused leaving the three-furlong marker, raced three wide into the drive, was outkicked in deep stretch and was clear for third. AFRICAN PRINCE raced closest to the loose leading pair through decent early fractions, advanced leaving the second turn, ran evenly in the final furlong, was a bit erratic in the late stages and could not impact the top three in the end. KID STOLE A KISS took back off of the decent early pace, saved ground to the top of the lane and did not threaten. RANCHO RED sent to establish the early advantage, set prompted fractions through the backstretch run, came under pressure from TIGER'S ARROW nearing the quarter marker, was overtaken by that rival leaving the far turn and faded in the drive. TAKE THE TWO TEN allowed to settle, lagged through the backstretch run, asked for run nearing the top of the lane and lacked a late response.

ENTRY.NAME: Lookout Point
ENTRY.COMMENT: off pace,saved ground,roused 4wide,closed fast,up in time

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 2 6F All Weather Track CR: 70. Claiming Purse 13400. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Weight, 123 lbs. Claiming Price $4,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MISTICAL SURPRISE away in good order, contested the early pace with DADDYS NINA, lost ground to that rival nearing the top of the lane, chased to mid-stretch, responded to firm urging inside of the furlong marker, re-rallied and took command inside of the sixteenth-marker and determinedly held on in the final strides to prevail. DIZZY DAZMURA broke in at the start and was away a step slowly, chased the moderate early pace, raced three wide on the turn, swung five wide for the drive, made a steady gain through the final furlong, came within aim of MISTICAL SURPRISE in deep stretch and just missed for the win in the final strides, while besting the rest. GOLD RUSH GAL allowed to settle while outside of rivals in the early going, roused five wide into the stretch run, was not able to impact the top two in the late stages but closed well and was up for show in the final strides. LADY BLACKBIRD forwardly placed in the early stages, chased the moderate pace while three wide to the quarter marker, advanced to vie for the lead in mid-stretch, could not keep pace in the late stages, weakened in deep stretch and was just edged for third. PETE'S INFERNO hit the gate leaving the start then was shuffled back in the first few strides and was away slowly, took back off of the decent early pace, raced two wide on the turn, angled four wide in upper stretch, encountered traffic inside of the furlong marker, remained blocked to the sixteenth-pole and finished evenly in the late stages. DADDYS NINA engaged with MISTICAL SURPRISE in the early stages and disputed the moderate early pace, dueled outside of that rival on the turn, took a narrow advantage into upper stretch, battled to the furlong marker and gave way in the late stages. BIG STORM KITTY chased the moderate early pace, lost ground while two wide on the turn and did not offer a late rally.

ENTRY.NAME: Dizzy Dazmura
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke in start,chase 3wide,5wide rally,steady gain,missed,2nd bst

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 3 1M All Weather Track CR: 73. Claiming Purse 14500. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Weight, 123 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000 (Maiden, Claiming And Starter Races For $4,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LIGHT UP away in good order, took back off of the modest early pace, well placed through the backstretch run, roused three wide nearing the quarter marker, assumed command leaving the far turn, extended the lead to mid-stretch, drew clear nearing the sixteenth-marker, Rivera lost his crop inside of the sixteenth-marker, kept to task in deep stretch and lasted over the quickly oncoming runner-up. SHANGHAI MIST allowed to settle, a bit keen along the first turn, settled along the backstretch run, trailed to the far turn, came in tight nearing the top of the lane and encountered traffic in upper stretch, shifted out and found racing room in mid-stretch, closed with a rush in the final stages and just missed for the win while securing the place in the final strides. MOONSHINE CAT rated off of the pace while traveling in the second flight, advanced three wide on the far turn, lost ground in upper stretch, re-rallied in the final furlong, finished well and just missed for place, while securing show in the final strides. ARISTEIA assumed command leaving the break, set modest fractions through the backstretch run, came under pressure nearing the quarter marker, was overtaken by LIGHT UP leaving the far turn, stayed within aim while chasing that rival to mid-stretch, was outfinished in the late stages and was just edged for third. FLIPLIT forwardly placed in the early going, stalked the modest fractions from the rail to the second turn, lost ground nearing the furlong pole, was gaining in deep stretch but could not match strides with the leaders in the final stages. COCOA CENTS prominent into the first turn, raced close to the modest early pace, advanced to attend to the pace to the second turn, lost position in upper stretch, showed good late interest but did not offer the needed late response. SMILING MELANIE allowed to settle while not far back, raced outside of rivals to the second turn, came four wide to the quarter marker and lacked a late rally.

ENTRY.OWNER: Bach Martin W and Weiner Daniel

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 4 1M All Weather Track CR: 83. Claiming Purse 14000. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE NOVEMBER 1 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Weight, 123 lbs. Claiming Price $4,000 (Claiming And Starter Races For $3,500 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: EXCLUSIVE SPEAKER asked to show early speed and was sent to dictate terms early on, was confronted by ON RAGLAN ROAD along the backstretch run, was headed by that rival nearing the top of the lane, battled to mid-stretch, lost the lead inside of the furlong marker, fought back from the inside while dueling to the wire in deep stretch and determinedly prevailed in the final strides. ON RAGLAN ROAD prominent into the first turn, stalked the early pace then advanced to press the decent fractions to the second turn, came to even terms with EXCLUSIVE SPEAKER nearing the quarter marker, battled to mid-stretch and took a narrow lead inside of the furlong pole, dueled to the outside of EXCLUSIVE SPEAKER to deep stretch and was gamely bested in the final strides, while well clear of the rest for second. ECOLOGIST took back to race in the second flight, well placed to the far turn, roused three wide into the stretch run, was not able to impact the top two in the late stages but rallied in deep stretch and outfinished WILL IS CHILL to secure third. WILL IS CHILL broke out at the start and crowded AWE, was allowed to settle, roused leaving the three-furlong marker, saved ground to the top of the lane, closed willingly in the late stages and just missed for third in the final strides. AWE crowded at the start and was away a step slowly, was allowed to settle in the early going, advanced along the backstretch run, well placed into the second turn, chased the top pair into the stretch and lacked a late rally. BROKEN FINGER came in a bit tight into the first turn,stalked the decent early fractions, saved ground to the quarter marker and tired in the drive. ORCZY (IRE) unhurried in the early stages, lost contact along the second turn and was not a factor.

ENTRY.NAME: Broken Finger
ENTRY.OWNER: Rivera Leobardo R and Sosa Manuela Franco

ENTRY.NAME: On Raglan Road
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked early pace,pressed 2nd turn,dueled stretch,gamely bested

ENTRY.NAME: Awe
ENTRY.COMMENT: crowded st,4wide 1st turn,well placed,no late rally

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 5 5 1/2F All Weather Track CR: 99. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 32000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON $15,000 TWICE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR STATE BRED OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $62,500. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races Since November 1 Allowed 3 lbs. A Race Since Then Allowed 5 lbs. Claiming Price $62,500 (Maiden, Claiming And Starter Races For $50,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ALWAYS SEEKING away in good order, tracked the solid early pace, advanced to stalk three wide nearing the quarter marker, loomed in upper stretch, overtook CAROLINA MIA nearing the furlong marker, drew clear under mild urging in the final sixteenth and was geared down in the final strides. LUXURY LINER close up to the early pace, pressed the solid fractions while outside of CAROLINA MIA, chased that rival to mid-stretch, could not keep pace with ALWAYS SEEKING inside of the furlong marker and outfinished CAROLINA MIA in the final stages to secure second. CAROLINA MIA showed good early speed, set the pressured pace to the turn, carved out solid fractions to the quarter marker, was set down for the drive while holding foes at bay in upper stretch, could not hold off ALWAYS SEEKING nearing the furlong marker, weakened in the late stages and was outfinished for second, while holding for third. CODE RIBBON unhurried in the early going, raced three wide into the stretch, lacked a late kick and just missed for third in the final strides. THAT'S AMARE chased the fast early pace, saved ground to the top of the lane, could not keep pace in the drive and tired.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 6 5 1/2F All Weather Track CR: 86. Claiming Purse 15000. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE NOVEMBER 1 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Weight, 123 lbs. Claiming Price $6,250 (Maiden, Claiming And Starter Races For $5,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: EXCESSIVE CAT bobbled slightly at the start but showed good early speed and dictated terms to the turn, was pressed by PHANTOM DROP to the quarter marker, shook free of that rival leaving the turn, drew clear to mid-stretch and drew away under mild urging in the final sixteenth. PHANTOM DROP broke sharply then lost the early lead to EXCESSIVE CAT, tracked that rival to the turn, pressed the solid pace to the quarter marker, could not keep pace with the winner in the drive and held for second in the late stages. CONTINENTAL UNION allowed to settle in the early stages, saved ground on the turn, roused in upper stretch, found his best stride late, closed well in the final sixteenth and just missed for second, while clear of the rest for third. MUAY THAI (IRE) chased from the second flight in the early going, raced two wide between runners to the quarter marker, encountered traffic in upper stretch, raced on the left lead in the drive and lacked a late response. TIZ VICIOUS chased the fast early pace, advanced three wide on the turn, was outrun in upper stretch and lacked a late rally. EMERALD MAGIC was unhurried in the early stages, chased three wide on the turn and did not threaten in the late stages. R M C HOOK'EM was forwardly placed in the early going, steadied off of heels nearing the half-mile marker, stalked the fast pace from the rail on the turn and tired in the stretch drive.

ENTRY.NAME: Excessive Cat
ENTRY.COMMENT: bobbled start,showed speed,shook free 3/16,drew away late

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 7 1M All Weather Track CR: 91. Claiming Purse 26000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since November 1 Allowed 3 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000, if for $22,500, allowed 2 lbs. (Maiden, Claiming And Starter Races For $20,000 Or Less Not C onsidered In Allowances).

CLAIM.OWNER: Huntertown Farm LLC and Calvario Samuel

RACE.FOOTNOTES: LA VIKINA prominent in the early stages, stalked the decent fractions to the half-mile marker, roused two wide nearing the quarter pole, overtook SEN SEN leaving the far turn, extended the lead to mid-stretch and kept to task in the late stages to prove best. SCHERZO (GB) forwardly placed into the first turn, tracked the decent pace from a ground saving position through the backstretch run, angled three wide approaching the top of the lane, ran evenly to mid-stretch, was outkicked by the winner in the final stages and held well in the end to secure the place. GETTIN SIDEWAYS took back in the early going, advanced along the backstretch run and was well positioned into the far turn, raced two then three wide nearing the quarter marker, caught a bit of traffic turning into the stretch and angled back inside for the drive, ran evenly to mid-stretch and was outfinished for place, while holding safely for show. IMPERIAL CREED allowed to settle, raced outside of rivals while advancing on the backstretch run, mounted a four wide bid nearing the top of the stretch, ran evenly to the furlong grounds and flattened out in the late stages. SEN SEN a bit fractious in the gate, was hustled to establish the early lead, dictated terms while carving out decent fractions through the backstretch run, came under pressure nearing the quarter marker, was collared by LA VIKINA leaving the second turn and gave way in the drive. I'LL DO IT FOR YOU never far back in the early running, could not keep pace on the second turn and tired in the stretch.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 8 5 1/2F All Weather Track CR: 74. Maiden Claiming Purse 17000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000, if for $22,500, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MOMO'S KIDDO shied from SGT POWELL when that one came in at the break, kept to the rear of the field under some light restraint, moved up into contention on the turn, swung four wide into the stretch, found clear run and launched a bold rally down the middle of the course to get up just in time over a game opponent. MURLOC BAY was first away from the break, opened up a clear lead through the turn with a host of challengers in close pursuit, opened up in the stretch and ran on well only to be caught in the final yards. FLY WICKED EAGLE fractious in the gate, got a good break and was among the leaders early, then lost a bit of ground on the turn, came under a hard ride from the quarter pole then found a second wind, finishing well to gain third. DR LOW KEY was off-balance at the break then ducked in and was bumped in turn by FLY WICKED EAGLE to the inside then by MURLOC BAY to the outside, steadied, then rushed up to join the pace, came under heavy pressure passing the quarter pole, ran on the wrong lead through most of the stretch and flattened out. LOKI OF ASGARD broke alertly but outrun in the early stages, came under a ride with three furlongs to go, swung five wide for the stretch run and finished with some interest but was unable to improve position. SGT POWELL broke in at the start and quickly corrected, was not asked for much speed early and settled in a tracking position behind the early pace, was in striking position through the turn but boxed in, got clear at the head of stretch then was bumped by FLY WICKED EAGLE then unable to find a good rhythm after that and lacked a rally. GATO NEGRO broke a bit slowly, saved ground throughout and finished evenly while never a threat. BOLD TALKER broke well and was among the leaders down the backstretch, loomed a threat to the top of the stretch but then tired and had little to offer down the stretch.

ENTRY.NAME: Momo's Kiddo
ENTRY.COMMENT: reserved early, loomed turn, 4wide bid stretch, bold late rally
